<h1 property="name" id="wb-cont" class="gc-thickline">Determined whether the persons are related?</h1>

 <div class="alert alert-info">
<p>Content has been updated for clarity, completeness and plain language. <strong>No changes were made to the current CRA administrative policy. </strong></p>

</div>

<section aria-modal="true" class="modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-4283">	<div class="modal-body">				<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"><p>Have you determined whether the persons are related?</p></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p>Use this mapping to help determine if parties are dealing at arm's length with&nbsp;each other.&nbsp;</p>

<p><span class="fa fa-exclamation-triangle fa-fw" style="font-size:14px">&nbsp;</span>Person includes:&nbsp;</p>

<ul>
	<li>an individual</li>
	<li>a corporation</li>
	<li>any entity listed in subsection 149(1)</li>
	<li>heirs, executors, liquidators of a succession, administrators or other legal representatives of such a person</li>
	<li>a&nbsp;partnership, for GST/HST purposes, but <strong>not</strong> for income tax purposes</li>
</ul>

<p style="margin-left:40px">Examples of entities listed in subsection 149(1) include municipalities, Crown corporations, registered charities, universities, athletic associations, labour organizations, non-profit organizations and trusts.</p>

<p><span class="fa fa-exclamation-triangle fa-fw" style="font-size:14px">&nbsp;</span>Related persons are deemed <strong>not</strong> to deal at arm's length with each other.</p>

<p>This mapping covers the most common situations. It does not take into account all exceptions/situations and is only provided as a guideline. <strong>It does not replace the law</strong>.<span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:9.0pt"><span style="background-color:white"><span style="line-height:107%"><span><span style="color:#333333"></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-4">No - Determine if persons are related</a></li><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-4874" id="wb-auto-5">Yes, the persons are not related - Determine if unrelated persons deal at arm's length</a></li><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-85455" id="wb-auto-6">Resources and references                                                                                        </a></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-4775">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-7">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"><p>Who are the persons?</p></h2>		<p class="dt-question"></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-4779" id="wb-auto-8">Individuals</a></li><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-4778" id="wb-auto-9">Corporations</a></li><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-4780" id="wb-auto-10">A corporation and a person (or group of persons)</a></li><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-4818" id="wb-auto-11">Trusts                                              </a></li><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-4781" id="wb-auto-12">Partnerships                                                                                                                                                         </a></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-4779">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-13">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-14">Who are the persons?</a> – Individuals</li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"><p>Are the individuals&nbsp;in any of the <strong>4</strong> situations?</p></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p>Individuals&nbsp;in any of the <strong>4</strong> situations are related to each other.</p>

<p><strong>ACT</strong>:</p>

<ul>
	<li>Blood relationship: <a href="http://www.laws-lois.justice.gc.ca/eng/acts/I-3.3/section-251.html#s-251ss-(6)ID0EFCA" onclick="window.open(this.href, '', 'resizable=no,status=no,location=no,toolbar=no,menubar=no,fullscreen=no,scrollbars=no,dependent=no,width=1200,left=300,height=600,top=50'); return false;">251(6)(a)</a></li>
	<li>Marriage: <a href="http://www.laws-lois.justice.gc.ca/eng/acts/I-3.3/section-251.html#s-251ss-(6)ID0EFCA" onclick="window.open(this.href, '', 'resizable=no,status=no,location=no,toolbar=no,menubar=no,fullscreen=no,scrollbars=no,dependent=no,width=1200,left=300,height=600,top=50'); return false;">251(6)(b)</a></li>
	<li>Common-law: <a href="http://www.laws-lois.justice.gc.ca/eng/acts/I-3.3/section-251.html#s-251ss-(6)ID0EFCA" onclick="window.open(this.href, '', 'resizable=no,status=no,location=no,toolbar=no,menubar=no,fullscreen=no,scrollbars=no,dependent=no,width=1200,left=300,height=600,top=50'); return false;">251(6)(b.1)</a> and <a href="http://www.laws-lois.justice.gc.ca/eng/acts/I-3.3/section-248.html#s-248" onclick="window.open(this.href, '', 'resizable=no,status=no,location=no,toolbar=no,menubar=no,fullscreen=no,scrollbars=no,dependent=no,width=1200,left=300,height=600,top=50'); return false;">248(1)</a></li>
	<li>Adoption: <a href="http://www.laws-lois.justice.gc.ca/eng/acts/I-3.3/section-251.html#s-251ss-(6)ID0EFCA" onclick="window.open(this.href, '', 'resizable=no,status=no,location=no,toolbar=no,menubar=no,fullscreen=no,scrollbars=no,dependent=no,width=1200,left=300,height=600,top=50'); return false;">251(6)(c)</a></li>
	<li>Extension of the word child: <a href="http://www.laws-lois.justice.gc.ca/eng/acts/I-3.3/section-252.html#s-252ss-(2)ID0EIEA" onclick="window.open(this.href, '', 'resizable=no,status=no,location=no,toolbar=no,menubar=no,fullscreen=no,scrollbars=no,dependent=no,width=1200,left=300,height=600,top=50'); return false;">252(1)</a></li>
	<li>Extension of relationship: <a href="http://www.laws-lois.justice.gc.ca/eng/acts/I-3.3/section-252.html#s-252ss-(2)ID0EIEA" onclick="window.open(this.href, '', 'resizable=no,status=no,location=no,toolbar=no,menubar=no,fullscreen=no,scrollbars=no,dependent=no,width=1200,left=300,height=600,top=50'); return false;">252(2)</a></li>
</ul></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-94252" id="wb-auto-15">Yes</a></li><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-452688" id="wb-auto-16">No   </a></li><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-949395" id="wb-auto-17">Situation 1 - Blood relationship</a></li><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-777413" id="wb-auto-18">Situation 2 - Marriage                        </a></li><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-633012" id="wb-auto-19">Situation 3 - Common-law                         </a></li><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-831709" id="wb-auto-20">Situation 4 - Adoption                                      </a></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-94252">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-21">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-22">Who are the persons?</a> – Individuals</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4779" id="wb-auto-23">Are the individuals&nbsp;in any of the <strong>4</strong> situations?</a> – Yes</li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p><strong>RESULT</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-fw fa-times-circle" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:14px">&nbsp;</span>The individuals are related to each other. They<strong> do not </strong>deal at arm's length with each other.</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-exclamation-triangle fa-fw" style="font-size:14px">&nbsp;</span>In a worker/employer situation, related individuals may be deemed to deal at arm's length if it is reasonable to conclude that the employer and worker would have entered a similar contract if they had been dealing at arm's length giving consideration to:</p>

<ul style="margin-left:40px">
	<li>remuneration</li>
	<li>work hours</li>
	<li>the terms and conditions of employment</li>
	<li>the nature and importance of the work performed</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>ACT</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">Not dealing at arm's length: 251(1)(a)</p></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><button class="btn btn-success popup-modal-dismiss" type="button">End</button></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-452688">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-24">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-25">Who are the persons?</a> – Individuals</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4779" id="wb-auto-26">Are the individuals&nbsp;in any of the <strong>4</strong> situations?</a> – No   </li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p><strong>RESULT</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">The individuals are <strong>not</strong> related to each other. They may deal at arm's length with each other.</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-hand-o-right" style="color:#009900; font-size:18px">&nbsp;</span>To find out whether they deal at arm's length, go to <strong>Determine if unrelated persons deal at arm's length</strong>.</p>

<p><strong>ACT</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">Unrelated persons are dealing at arm's length is a question of fact: 251(1)(c)</p></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><button class="btn btn-success popup-modal-dismiss" type="button">End</button></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-949395">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-27">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-28">Who are the persons?</a> – Individuals</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4779" id="wb-auto-29">Are the individuals&nbsp;in any of the <strong>4</strong> situations?</a> – Situation 1 - Blood relationship</li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p><strong>RESULT</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">The following individuals are related by blood:</p>

<ul style="margin-left:40px">
	<li>a parent and a child (or other descendant, such as a grandchild or a great-grandchild)</li>
	<li>a brother and a sister</li>
</ul>

<p style="margin-left:40px">Blood relatives <strong>do not </strong>include more distant relatives such as aunts, uncles, nieces, nephews or cousins.</p>

<p><strong>EXAMPLE</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">Zuly and Silvia are sisters. Zuly is married to Juan and Silvia is married to Yuri. Zuly and Silvia are related because they are sisters. Zuly and Juan are related by marriage. Silvia and Yuri are related by marriage. As a result of their marriages, Yuri is related to Zuly and Juan is related to Silvia, but Juan and Yuri are not related to each other.&nbsp;</p></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><button class="btn btn-success popup-modal-dismiss" type="button">End</button></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-777413">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-30">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-31">Who are the persons?</a> – Individuals</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4779" id="wb-auto-32">Are the individuals&nbsp;in any of the <strong>4</strong> situations?</a> – Situation 2 - Marriage                        </li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p><strong>RESULT</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">Two individuals are related to each other if they are legally married to each other. They are also related to anyone connected by blood relationship (parents and siblings) to their spouse. They may be related by adoption to any children of their spouse, depending on the circumstances.&nbsp;For more information, see <strong>Situation 4 - Adoption</strong>.&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">If the marriage is dissolved because of divorce or death of a spouse, the individual ceases to be connected by marriage.</p>

<p><strong>EXAMPLE</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">Jack and Jill were married on June 15, 2016. Later, their marriage broke down and they were legally divorced on October 1, 2019. For the period from the date of marriage until the date of their legal divorce, Jack and Jill were related to each other as well as their respective parents-in-law and brothers/sisters-in-law.</p></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><button class="btn btn-success popup-modal-dismiss" type="button">End</button></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-633012">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-33">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-34">Who are the persons?</a> – Individuals</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4779" id="wb-auto-35">Are the individuals&nbsp;in any of the <strong>4</strong> situations?</a> – Situation 3 - Common-law                         </li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p><strong>RESULT</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">Two individuals are related to each other if they are in a common-law partnership with&nbsp;each other. CRA considers that two individuals are in a common-law partnership if:</p>

<ul>
	<li>they live together in a conjugal relationship and have done so for a continuous period of at least 12 months</li>
	<li>they live together in a conjugal relationship and&nbsp;have a child together (this includes through adoption), in which case the 12-month period does not apply</li>
</ul>

<p style="margin-left:40px">They are also related to anyone connected by blood relationship (parents and siblings) to their common-law partner. They may also be related by adoption to any children of their common-law partner, depending on the circumstances. For more information, see <strong>Situation 4 - Adoption</strong>.&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">If there is a breakdown in the relationship, they are considered to continue to live in a common-law partnership until they have lived separate and apart for 90 consecutive days.</p>

<p><strong>EXAMPLE</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">Jack and Jill had a child together. They began living together in a conjugal relationship 1 month before their child was born. They are common-law partners as of the day their child is born. If they did not have a child together, they would not be common-law partners until they lived together for 12 months.</p></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><button class="btn btn-success popup-modal-dismiss" type="button">End</button></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-831709">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-36">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-37">Who are the persons?</a> – Individuals</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4779" id="wb-auto-38">Are the individuals&nbsp;in any of the <strong>4</strong> situations?</a> – Situation 4 - Adoption                                      </li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p><strong>RESULT</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">Two individuals are related to each other through adoption if one individual is the adopted child of the other. In addition to their parents, the child is also related to their siblings, grandparents and great-grandparents.</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">Adoption includes legal adoption and de facto adoption.&nbsp;The following factors are considered when&nbsp;determining whether a de facto adoption exists:</p>

<ul style="margin-left:40px">
	<li>actual control and custody</li>
	<li>an exercise of parental care and responsibility on a continuing basis</li>
	<li>dependency</li>
	<li>proximity to each other</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>EXAMPLE</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">Jack and Jill are related to two of their children by blood (Mark and Tom) and one of their children by adoption (Eleanor).</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">Eleanor is related to her siblings (Mark and Tom) and her four grandparents (the parents of Jack and Jill). &nbsp;</p></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><button class="btn btn-success popup-modal-dismiss" type="button">End</button></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-4778">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-39">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-40">Who are the persons?</a> – Corporations</li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"><p>Are the persons controlling each corporation related?</p></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p>To find out if one corporation is related to another corporation, you must determine who controls each corporation.&nbsp;</p>

<p><span class="fa fa-exclamation-triangle fa-fw" style="font-size:14px">&nbsp;</span> For a single person to control a corporation, the person&nbsp;<strong>must have more than 50% (50% + 1)&nbsp;</strong>of the voting shares.</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><strong>EXAMPLE</strong>:&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">If 1,000,000 voting shares have been issued, a person would have to have 500,001 of the voting shares to control the corporation on their own.</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">The class of shares (and the rights attached to the shares) are described in the Articles of Incorporation. They can be changed only by amending the articles.</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">If only one class of shares have been issued, all shares in the corporation have the same rights. In this case, all shares would be voting shares.</p>

<p>For more information on shares and how they work, see&nbsp;<a href="https://www.ic.gc.ca/eic/site/cd-dgc.nsf/eng/cs06644.html" rel="external" target="_blank">Share structure and shareholders</a>.</p></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-462507" id="wb-auto-41">Both corporations are controlled by the same person</a></li><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-4793" id="wb-auto-42">Each corporation is controlled by a different person</a></li><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-145120" id="wb-auto-43">Both corporations are controlled by the same group of persons</a></li><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-4785" id="wb-auto-44">Each corporation is controlled by a different group of persons</a></li><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-4784" id="wb-auto-45">One corporation is controlled by one person and the other corporation is controlled by a group of persons</a></li><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-781218" id="wb-auto-46">Each corporation is related to the same third corporation                                                                                            </a></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-462507">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-47">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-48">Who are the persons?</a> – Corporations</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4778" id="wb-auto-49">Are the persons controlling each corporation related?</a> – Both corporations are controlled by the same person</li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p><strong>RESULT</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-fw fa-times-circle" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:14px">&nbsp;</span>The corporations are related to each other. They <strong>do not </strong>deal at arm's length with each other.</p>

<div style="background:#eeeeee; border:1px solid #cccccc; margin-left:40px; padding:5px 10px">Person includes a partnership&nbsp;for the purpose of:<br>
&nbsp; &nbsp;-&nbsp;CEWS and CERS claims<br>
&nbsp; &nbsp;- GST/HST</div>

<p><br>
<strong>EXAMPLE</strong>:</p>

<ul>
	<li>Bob owns 100% of the shares of A Corp.</li>
	<li>Bob owns 51% of the voting shares of B Corp.</li>
	<li>Bob controls both corporations since he&nbsp;owns more than 50% of the voting shares in each.&nbsp;</li>
</ul>

<p style="margin-left:40px">A Corp and B Corp are related to each other.</p>

<p><strong>ACT</strong>:</p>

<ul>
	<li>251(2)(c)(i)</li>
	<li>Not dealing at arm's length: 251(1)(a)</li>
</ul></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><button class="btn btn-success popup-modal-dismiss" type="button">End</button></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-4793">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-50">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-51">Who are the persons?</a> – Corporations</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4778" id="wb-auto-52">Are the persons controlling each corporation related?</a> – Each corporation is controlled by a different person</li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"><p>Are the two corporations related to each other?<a href="https://cc-ua.omega.dce-eir.net/english/sard/ots/dtg/flow/crud_decision/151/4783#4775,4778,4783"><em> </em></a></p></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p><strong>Related group</strong>&nbsp;means that each member in a group of persons is related to every other member of the group.</p>

<p><strong>Unrelated group</strong>&nbsp;means a group of persons that is not a related group. </p>

<p><strong>ACT</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">251(4)</p></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-561599" id="wb-auto-53">The person that controls one corporation is related to the person that controls the other corporation</a></li><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-390284" id="wb-auto-54">The person that controls one corporation is not related to the person that controls the other corporation</a></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-561599">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-55">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-56">Who are the persons?</a> – Corporations</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4778" id="wb-auto-57">Are the persons controlling each corporation related?</a> – Each corporation is controlled by a different person</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4793" id="wb-auto-58">Are the two corporations related to each other?</a><a href="https://cc-ua.omega.dce-eir.net/english/sard/ots/dtg/flow/crud_decision/151/4783#4775,4778,4783"><em> </em></a> – The person that controls one corporation is related to the person that controls the other corporation</li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p><strong>RESULT</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-fw fa-times-circle" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:14px">&nbsp;</span>The two corporations are related to each other. They do <strong>not </strong>deal at arm's length with each other.</p>

<div style="background:#eeeeee; border:1px solid #cccccc; margin-left:40px; padding:5px 10px">Person includes a partnership&nbsp;for the purpose of:<br>
&nbsp; &nbsp;-&nbsp;CEWS and CERS claims<br>
&nbsp; &nbsp;- GST/HST</div>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>EXAMPLE</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">The voting shares of A Corp and B Corp are owned as follows:</p>

<table align="left" border="1" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="3" style="margin-left:60px">
	<thead>
		<tr>
			<th scope="col" style="width:80px">A Corp</th>
			<th scope="col" style="width:40px">%</th>
			<th scope="col" style="width:80px">B Corp</th>
			<th scope="col" style="width:40px">%</th>
		</tr>
	</thead>
	<tbody>
		<tr>
			<td style="width:80px">Bob</td>
			<td style="width:40px">60%</td>
			<td style="width:80px">Phillip</td>
			<td style="width:40px">51%</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td style="width:80px">Henry</td>
			<td style="width:40px">20%</td>
			<td style="width:80px">Rachel</td>
			<td style="width:40px">39%</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td style="width:80px">Sadie</td>
			<td style="width:40px">20%</td>
			<td style="width:80px">Vicky</td>
			<td style="width:40px">10%</td>
		</tr>
	</tbody>
</table>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">&nbsp;</p>

<ul style="margin-left:40px">
	<li>Phillip is married to Bob's sister. As brothers-in-law, Bob and Phillip are related to each other;&nbsp;and Rachel is&nbsp;related to each of them.</li>
	<li>Bob controls A Corp since he owns more than 50% of the voting shares.</li>
	<li>Phillip&nbsp;controls B Corp since he owns more than 50% of the voting shares.&nbsp;</li>
	<li>The person (Bob) who controls A Corp is related to the person (Phillip) who&nbsp;controls B Corp.</li>
</ul>

<p style="margin-left:40px">A Corp is related to B Corp</p>

<p><strong>ACT</strong>:</p>

<ul>
	<li>251(2)(c)(i)</li>
	<li>Not dealing at arm's length: 251(1)(a)</li>
</ul></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><button class="btn btn-success popup-modal-dismiss" type="button">End</button></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-390284">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-59">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-60">Who are the persons?</a> – Corporations</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4778" id="wb-auto-61">Are the persons controlling each corporation related?</a> – Each corporation is controlled by a different person</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4793" id="wb-auto-62">Are the two corporations related to each other?</a><a href="https://cc-ua.omega.dce-eir.net/english/sard/ots/dtg/flow/crud_decision/151/4783#4775,4778,4783"><em> </em></a> – The person that controls one corporation is not related to the person that controls the other corporation</li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p><strong>RESULT</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">The two corporations are<strong> not </strong>related to each other.&nbsp;They may deal at arm's length with each other.&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-hand-o-right" style="color:#009900; font-size:18px">&nbsp;</span>To find out whether they deal at arm's length, go to <strong>Determine if unrelated persons deal at arm's length</strong>.</p>

<div style="background:#eeeeee; border:1px solid #cccccc; margin-left:40px; padding:5px 10px">Person includes a partnership&nbsp;for the purpose of:<br>
&nbsp; &nbsp;-&nbsp;CEWS and CERS claims<br>
&nbsp; &nbsp;- GST/HST</div>

<p style="margin-left:40px">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>EXAMPLE</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">The voting shares of A Corp and B Corp are owned as follows:</p>

<table align="left" border="1" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="1" style="margin-left:60px">
	<thead>
		<tr>
			<th scope="col" style="width:80px">A Corp</th>
			<th scope="col" style="width:40px">%</th>
			<th scope="col" style="width:80px">B Corp</th>
			<th scope="col" style="width:40px">%</th>
		</tr>
	</thead>
	<tbody>
		<tr>
			<td style="width:80px">Bob</td>
			<td style="width:40px">60%</td>
			<td style="width:80px">Phillip</td>
			<td style="width:40px">51%</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td style="width:80px">Henry</td>
			<td style="width:40px">20%</td>
			<td style="width:80px">Rachel</td>
			<td style="width:40px">39%</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td style="width:80px">Sadie</td>
			<td style="width:40px">20%</td>
			<td style="width:80px">Vicky</td>
			<td style="width:40px">10%</td>
		</tr>
	</tbody>
</table>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<ul style="margin-left:40px">
	<li>Bob, Henry and Sadie are<strong> not </strong>related to each other.</li>
	<li>Phillip, Rachel and Vicky are<strong> not</strong> related to each other.</li>
	<li>Bob controls A Corp since he owns more than 50% of the voting shares.</li>
	<li>Phillip controls B Corp since he owns more than 50% of the voting shares.</li>
	<li>Bob and Rachel are married to each other.</li>
	<li>Although Bob and Rachel are related to each other, since Rachel does not own more than 50% of the voting shares in B Corp, she does not control it.</li>
	<li>Since Bob and Phillip are<strong> not </strong>related to each other, the person (Bob) who controls A Corp is <strong>not </strong>related to the person (Phillip) who controls B Corp.</li>
</ul>

<p style="margin-left:40px">A Corp is <strong>not</strong> related to B Corp</p>

<p><strong>ACT</strong>:</p>

<ul>
	<li>251(2)(c)(i)</li>
	<li>Unrelated persons are dealing at arm's length is a question of fact: 251(1)(c)</li>
</ul></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><button class="btn btn-success popup-modal-dismiss" type="button">End</button></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-145120">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-63">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-64">Who are the persons?</a> – Corporations</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4778" id="wb-auto-65">Are the persons controlling each corporation related?</a> – Both corporations are controlled by the same group of persons</li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p><strong>RESULT</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-fw fa-times-circle" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:14px">&nbsp;</span>The corporations are related to each other. They <strong>do not </strong>deal at arm's length with each other.</p>

<div style="background:#eeeeee; border:1px solid #cccccc; margin-left:40px; padding:5px 10px">Person includes a partnership&nbsp;for the purpose of:<br>
&nbsp; &nbsp;-&nbsp;CEWS and CERS claims<br>
&nbsp; &nbsp;- GST/HST</div>

<p><br>
<strong>EXAMPLE</strong>:</p>

<ul>
	<li>Bob, Rachel and Phillip each&nbsp;own&nbsp;1/3 of the voting&nbsp;shares of A Corp.</li>
	<li>Bob, Rachel and Vicky each&nbsp;own&nbsp;1/3 of the voting&nbsp;shares of B Corp.</li>
	<li>Bob and Rachel control&nbsp;both&nbsp;corporations since they own more than 50% of the voting shares in each.&nbsp;</li>
</ul>

<p style="margin-left:40px">A Corp and B Corp are related to each other.</p>

<p><strong>ACT</strong>:</p>

<ul>
	<li>251(2)(c)(i)</li>
	<li>Not dealing at arm's length: 251(1)(a)</li>
</ul></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><button class="btn btn-success popup-modal-dismiss" type="button">End</button></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-4785">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-66">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-67">Who are the persons?</a> – Corporations</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4778" id="wb-auto-68">Are the persons controlling each corporation related?</a> – Each corporation is controlled by a different group of persons</li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"><p>Are the two corporations related to each other?<a href="https://cc-ua.omega.dce-eir.net/english/sard/ots/dtg/flow/crud_decision/151/4784#4775,4778,4784"><em> </em></a></p></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p><strong>Related group</strong> means that each member in a group of persons is related to every other member of the group.</p>

<p><strong>Unrelated group</strong> means a group of persons that is not a related group. </p>

<p><strong>ACT</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">251(4)</p></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-440939" id="wb-auto-69">Any member of a related group that controls one corporation is related to each member of an unrelated group that controls the other corporation</a></li><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-452817" id="wb-auto-70">Each member of an unrelated group that controls one corporation is related to at least one member of an unrelated group that controls the other corporation</a></li><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-436460" id="wb-auto-71">It is not the case that each member of an unrelated group that controls one corporation is related to at least one member of an unrelated group that controls the other corporation</a></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-440939">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-72">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-73">Who are the persons?</a> – Corporations</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4778" id="wb-auto-74">Are the persons controlling each corporation related?</a> – Each corporation is controlled by a different group of persons</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4785" id="wb-auto-75">Are the two corporations related to each other?</a><a href="https://cc-ua.omega.dce-eir.net/english/sard/ots/dtg/flow/crud_decision/151/4784#4775,4778,4784"><em> </em></a> – Any member of a related group that controls one corporation is related to each member of an unrelated group that controls the other corporation</li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p><strong>RESULT</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-fw fa-times-circle" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:14px">&nbsp;</span>The two corporations are related to each other. They do <strong>not </strong>deal at arm's length with each other.</p>

<div style="background:#eeeeee; border:1px solid #cccccc; margin-left:40px; padding:5px 10px">Person includes a partnership&nbsp;for the purpose of:<br>
&nbsp; &nbsp;-&nbsp;CEWS and CERS claims<br>
&nbsp; &nbsp;- GST/HST</div>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>EXAMPLE</strong>:</p>

<ul>
	<li>Rachel has two sons, Phillip and Henry. Therefore, Rachel, Phillip and Henry are all related to each other.</li>
	<li>Phillip has a daughter, Sadie.</li>
	<li>Henry has a daughter, Vicky.</li>
	<li>Rachel, Phillip and Henry each own 1/3 of the voting shares in&nbsp;A Corp.</li>
	<li>Vicky and Sadie each own 50% of the shares of B Corp. Vicky and Sadie are <strong>not </strong>related to each other since they are cousins.</li>
	<li>Rachel is related to Vicky and Sadie since she is their grandmother.</li>
</ul>

<p style="margin-left:40px">A Corp and B Corp are related to each other, since:</p>

<ul style="margin-left:40px">
	<li>A Corp is controlled by a&nbsp;related group</li>
	<li>A member&nbsp;(Rachel) of the related group that controls A Corp&nbsp;is related to each member (Vicky and Sadie) of an unrelated group that controls B Corp</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>ACT</strong>:</p>

<ul>
	<li>251(2)(c)(iv)</li>
	<li>Not dealing at arm's length: 251(1)(a)</li>
</ul></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><button class="btn btn-success popup-modal-dismiss" type="button">End</button></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-452817">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-76">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-77">Who are the persons?</a> – Corporations</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4778" id="wb-auto-78">Are the persons controlling each corporation related?</a> – Each corporation is controlled by a different group of persons</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4785" id="wb-auto-79">Are the two corporations related to each other?</a><a href="https://cc-ua.omega.dce-eir.net/english/sard/ots/dtg/flow/crud_decision/151/4784#4775,4778,4784"><em> </em></a> – Each member of an unrelated group that controls one corporation is related to at least one member of an unrelated group that controls the other corporation</li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p><strong>RESULT</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-fw fa-times-circle" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:14px">&nbsp;</span>The two corporations are related to each other. They do <strong>not </strong>deal at arm's length with each other.</p>

<div style="background:#eeeeee; border:1px solid #cccccc; margin-left:40px; padding:5px 10px">Person includes a partnership&nbsp;for the purpose of:<br>
&nbsp; &nbsp;-&nbsp;CEWS and CERS claims<br>
&nbsp; &nbsp;- GST/HST</div>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>EXAMPLE</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">The voting shares of A Corp and B Corp are owned as follows:</p>

<table align="left" border="1" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="1" style="margin-left:60px">
	<thead>
		<tr>
			<th scope="col" style="width:74px">A Corp</th>
			<th scope="col" style="width:38px">%</th>
			<th scope="col" style="width:71px">B Corp</th>
			<th scope="col" style="width:39px">%</th>
		</tr>
	</thead>
	<tbody>
		<tr>
			<td style="width:74px">Bob</td>
			<td style="width:38px">33.3%&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>
			<td style="width:71px">Sadie</td>
			<td style="width:39px">33.3%&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td style="width:74px">Henry</td>
			<td style="width:38px">33.3%</td>
			<td style="width:71px">Rachel</td>
			<td style="width:39px">33.3%</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td style="width:74px">Phillip</td>
			<td style="width:38px">33.3%</td>
			<td style="width:71px">Vicky</td>
			<td style="width:39px">33.3%</td>
		</tr>
	</tbody>
</table>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<ul style="margin-left:40px">
	<li>Bob, Henry and Phillip are <strong>not</strong> related to each other. As a result, A Corp is not controlled by a related group.</li>
	<li>Sadie, Rachel and Vicky are <strong>not </strong>related to each other. As a result, B Corp is not controlled by a related group.</li>
	<li>Bob is married to Sadie.</li>
	<li>Henry is married to Rachel.</li>
	<li>Phillip is married to Vicky.</li>
</ul>

<p style="margin-left:40px">Each member of&nbsp;A Corp is related to at least one member of B Corp. Therefore,&nbsp;A Corp is related to B Corp</p>

<p><strong>ACT</strong>:</p>

<ul>
	<li>251(2)(c)(iii)</li>
	<li>Not dealing at arm's length: 251(1)(a)</li>
</ul></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><button class="btn btn-success popup-modal-dismiss" type="button">End</button></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-436460">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-80">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-81">Who are the persons?</a> – Corporations</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4778" id="wb-auto-82">Are the persons controlling each corporation related?</a> – Each corporation is controlled by a different group of persons</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4785" id="wb-auto-83">Are the two corporations related to each other?</a><a href="https://cc-ua.omega.dce-eir.net/english/sard/ots/dtg/flow/crud_decision/151/4784#4775,4778,4784"><em> </em></a> – It is not the case that each member of an unrelated group that controls one corporation is related to at least one member of an unrelated group that controls the other corporation</li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p><strong>RESULT</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">The two corporations are<strong> not </strong>related to each other.&nbsp;They may deal at arm's length with each other.&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-hand-o-right" style="color:#009900; font-size:18px">&nbsp;</span>To find out whether they deal at arm's length, go to <strong>Determine if unrelated persons deal at arm's length</strong>.</p>

<div style="background:#eeeeee; border:1px solid #cccccc; margin-left:40px; padding:5px 10px">Person includes a partnership&nbsp;for the purpose of:<br>
&nbsp; &nbsp;-&nbsp;CEWS and CERS claims<br>
&nbsp; &nbsp;- GST/HST</div>

<p style="margin-left:40px">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>EXAMPLE</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">The voting shares of A Corp and B Corp are owned as follows:</p>

<table align="left" border="1" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="1" style="margin-left:60px">
	<thead>
		<tr>
			<th scope="col" style="width:74px">A Corp</th>
			<th scope="col" style="width:38px">%</th>
			<th scope="col" style="width:71px">B Corp</th>
			<th scope="col" style="width:39px">%</th>
		</tr>
	</thead>
	<tbody>
		<tr>
			<td style="width:74px">Bob</td>
			<td style="width:38px">33.3%&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>
			<td style="width:71px">Sadie</td>
			<td style="width:39px">33.3%&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td style="width:74px">Henry</td>
			<td style="width:38px">33.3%</td>
			<td style="width:71px">Rachel</td>
			<td style="width:39px">33.3%</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td style="width:74px">Phillip</td>
			<td style="width:38px">33.3%</td>
			<td style="width:71px">Vicky</td>
			<td style="width:39px">33.3%</td>
		</tr>
	</tbody>
</table>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<ul style="margin-left:40px">
	<li>Bob is not related to Henry and Phillip, but Henry and Phillip are brothers.&nbsp;</li>
	<li>Sadie is not related to&nbsp;Rachel and Vicky, but Rachel and Vicky are sisters.</li>
	<li>Bob is married to Sadie.</li>
	<li>Although a&nbsp;related group controls each corporation, the related group that controls A Corp is not related to the related group that controls B Corp.</li>
	<li>Although Bob and Sadie are related to each other, neither of them controls their corporation.</li>
</ul>

<p style="margin-left:40px">A Corp is&nbsp;<strong>not</strong>&nbsp;related to B Corp.</p>

<p><strong>ACT</strong>:</p>

<ul>
	<li>251(2)(c)(i)</li>
	<li>Unrelated persons are dealing at arm's length is a question of fact: 251(1)(c)</li>
</ul></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><button class="btn btn-success popup-modal-dismiss" type="button">End</button></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-4784">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-84">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-85">Who are the persons?</a> – Corporations</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4778" id="wb-auto-86">Are the persons controlling each corporation related?</a> – One corporation is controlled by one person and the other corporation is controlled by a group of persons</li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"><p>Are the two corporations related to each other?<a href="https://cc-ua.omega.dce-eir.net/english/sard/ots/dtg/flow/crud_decision/151/4793#4775,4778,4793"><em> </em></a></p></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p><strong>Related group</strong> means that each member in a group of persons is related to every other member of the group.</p>

<p><strong>Unrelated group</strong> means a group of persons that is not a related group. </p>

<p><strong>ACT</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">251(4)</p></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-42257" id="wb-auto-87">The person who controls one corporation is related to one member of a related group that controls the other corporation</a></li><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-346708" id="wb-auto-88">The person who controls one corporation is related to every member of the unrelated group that controls the other corporation</a></li><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-321151" id="wb-auto-89">The person who controls one corporation is not related to any member of a group that would be able to control the other corporation                                           </a></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-42257">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-90">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-91">Who are the persons?</a> – Corporations</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4778" id="wb-auto-92">Are the persons controlling each corporation related?</a> – One corporation is controlled by one person and the other corporation is controlled by a group of persons</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4784" id="wb-auto-93">Are the two corporations related to each other?</a><a href="https://cc-ua.omega.dce-eir.net/english/sard/ots/dtg/flow/crud_decision/151/4793#4775,4778,4793"><em> </em></a> – The person who controls one corporation is related to one member of a related group that controls the other corporation</li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p><strong>RESULT</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-fw fa-times-circle" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:14px">&nbsp;</span>The two corporations are related to each other. They do <strong>not </strong>deal at arm's length with each other.</p>

<div style="background:#eeeeee; border:1px solid #cccccc; margin-left:40px; padding:5px 10px">Person includes a partnership&nbsp;for the purpose of:<br>
&nbsp; &nbsp;-&nbsp;CEWS and CERS claims<br>
&nbsp; &nbsp;- GST/HST</div>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>EXAMPLE</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">The voting shares of A Corp and B Corp are owned as follows:</p>

<table align="left" border="1" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="1" style="margin-left:60px">
	<thead>
		<tr>
			<th scope="col" style="text-align:left; width:115px">A Corp</th>
			<th scope="col" style="width:34px">%</th>
			<th scope="col" style="text-align:left; width:107px">B Corp</th>
			<th scope="col" style="width:42px">%</th>
		</tr>
	</thead>
	<tbody>
		<tr>
			<td style="width:115px">Bob</td>
			<td style="width:34px">60%</td>
			<td style="width:107px">Phillip</td>
			<td style="width:42px">33.3%</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td style="width:115px">Henry</td>
			<td style="width:34px">20%</td>
			<td style="width:107px">Rachel</td>
			<td style="width:42px">33.3%</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td style="width:115px">Sadie</td>
			<td style="width:34px">20%</td>
			<td style="width:107px">Vicky</td>
			<td style="width:42px">33.3%</td>
		</tr>
	</tbody>
</table>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">&nbsp;</p>

<ul style="margin-left:40px">
	<li>Bob and Rachel are related to each other. Rachel and Phillip are married.</li>
	<li>Bob controls A Corp since he owns more than 50% of the voting shares.</li>
	<li>Since Phillip and Rachel are related to each other and together they own more than 50% of the voting shares of B Corp, they are a related group that controls B Corp.</li>
	<li>The person (Bob) who controls A Corp is related to a person (Rachel) who is part of a related group that controls B Corp.</li>
</ul>

<p style="margin-left:40px">A Corp is related to B Corp</p>

<p><strong>ACT</strong>:</p>

<ul>
	<li>251(2)(c)(iii)</li>
	<li>Not dealing at arm's length: 251(1)(a)</li>
</ul></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><button class="btn btn-success popup-modal-dismiss" type="button">End</button></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-346708">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-94">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-95">Who are the persons?</a> – Corporations</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4778" id="wb-auto-96">Are the persons controlling each corporation related?</a> – One corporation is controlled by one person and the other corporation is controlled by a group of persons</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4784" id="wb-auto-97">Are the two corporations related to each other?</a><a href="https://cc-ua.omega.dce-eir.net/english/sard/ots/dtg/flow/crud_decision/151/4793#4775,4778,4793"><em> </em></a> – The person who controls one corporation is related to every member of the unrelated group that controls the other corporation</li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p><strong>RESULT</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-fw fa-times-circle" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:14px">&nbsp;</span>The two corporations are related to each other. They do <strong>not </strong>deal at arm's length with each other.</p>

<div style="background:#eeeeee; border:1px solid #cccccc; margin-left:40px; padding:5px 10px">Person includes a partnership&nbsp;for the purpose of:<br>
&nbsp; &nbsp;-&nbsp;CEWS and CERS claims<br>
&nbsp; &nbsp;- GST/HST</div>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>EXAMPLE</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">The voting shares of A Corp and B Corp are owned as follows:</p>

<table align="left" border="1" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="1" style="margin-left:60px">
	<thead>
		<tr>
			<th scope="col" style="text-align:left; width:115px">A Corp</th>
			<th scope="col" style="width:34px">%</th>
			<th scope="col" style="text-align:left; width:107px">B Corp</th>
			<th scope="col" style="width:42px">%</th>
		</tr>
	</thead>
	<tbody>
		<tr>
			<td style="width:115px">Bob</td>
			<td style="width:34px">60%</td>
			<td style="width:107px">Phillip</td>
			<td style="width:42px">33.3%</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td style="width:115px">Henry</td>
			<td style="width:34px">20%</td>
			<td style="width:107px">Rachel</td>
			<td style="width:42px">33.3%</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td style="width:115px">Sadie</td>
			<td style="width:34px">20%</td>
			<td style="width:107px">Vicky</td>
			<td style="width:42px">33.3%</td>
		</tr>
	</tbody>
</table>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">&nbsp;</p>

<ul style="margin-left:40px">
	<li>Bob is married to&nbsp;Rachel. Bob and Phillip are brothers. Phillip, Rachel and Vicky are <strong>not</strong> related to each other.</li>
	<li>Bob controls A Corp since he owns more than 50% of the voting shares.</li>
	<li>B Corp is <strong>not </strong>controlled by a related group. However, since Bob is related to both Phillip and Rachel&nbsp;and together they own more than 50% of the voting shares of B Corp, they are an unrelated group that controls B Corp.</li>
	<li>The person (Bob) who controls A Corp is related to each&nbsp;person (Phillip and Rachel) who is part of an&nbsp;unrelated group that controls B Corp.</li>
</ul>

<p style="margin-left:40px">A Corp is related to B Corp</p>

<p><strong>ACT</strong>:</p>

<ul>
	<li>251(2)(c)(iv)</li>
	<li>Not dealing at arm's length: 251(1)(a)</li>
</ul></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><button class="btn btn-success popup-modal-dismiss" type="button">End</button></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-321151">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-98">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-99">Who are the persons?</a> – Corporations</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4778" id="wb-auto-100">Are the persons controlling each corporation related?</a> – One corporation is controlled by one person and the other corporation is controlled by a group of persons</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4784" id="wb-auto-101">Are the two corporations related to each other?</a><a href="https://cc-ua.omega.dce-eir.net/english/sard/ots/dtg/flow/crud_decision/151/4793#4775,4778,4793"><em> </em></a> – The person who controls one corporation is not related to any member of a group that would be able to control the other corporation                                           </li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p><strong>RESULT</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">The two corporations are<strong> not </strong>related to each other.&nbsp;They may deal at arm's length with each other.&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-hand-o-right" style="color:#009900; font-size:18px">&nbsp;</span>To find out whether they deal at arm's length, go to <strong>Determine if unrelated persons deal at arm's length</strong>.</p>

<div style="background:#eeeeee; border:1px solid #cccccc; margin-left:40px; padding:5px 10px">Person includes a partnership&nbsp;for the purpose of:<br>
&nbsp; &nbsp;-&nbsp;CEWS and CERS claims<br>
&nbsp; &nbsp;- GST/HST</div>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>EXAMPLE</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">The voting shares of A Corp and B Corp are owned as follows:</p>

<table align="left" border="1" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="1" style="margin-left:60px">
	<thead>
		<tr>
			<th scope="col" style="text-align:left; width:115px">A Corp</th>
			<th scope="col" style="width:34px">%</th>
			<th scope="col" style="text-align:left; width:107px">B Corp</th>
			<th scope="col" style="width:42px">%</th>
		</tr>
	</thead>
	<tbody>
		<tr>
			<td style="width:115px">Bob</td>
			<td style="width:34px">60%</td>
			<td style="width:107px">Phillip</td>
			<td style="width:42px">51%</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td style="width:115px">Henry</td>
			<td style="width:34px">20%</td>
			<td style="width:107px">Rachel</td>
			<td style="width:42px">39%</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td style="width:115px">Sadie</td>
			<td style="width:34px">20%</td>
			<td style="width:107px">Vicky</td>
			<td style="width:42px">10%</td>
		</tr>
	</tbody>
</table>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">&nbsp;</p>

<ul style="margin-left:40px">
	<li>Bob, Henry and Sadie are<strong>&nbsp;not&nbsp;</strong>related to each other.</li>
	<li>Phillip is not related to&nbsp;Rachel and Vicky, however Rachel and Vicky are sisters.</li>
	<li>Bob controls A Corp since he owns more than 50% of the voting shares.</li>
	<li>Bob and Rachel are married to each other,&nbsp;so they are related to each other,. Rachel and Vicky are related to each other, but they do not enough voting shares to control&nbsp;B Corp.</li>
	<li>Although Bob is related to related group in B Corp, he is not related to a related group that controls B Corp.</li>
	<li>Phillip controls B Corp, but he is not related to any members in A Corp.</li>
</ul>

<p style="margin-left:40px">A Corp is&nbsp;<strong>not</strong>&nbsp;related to B Corp</p>

<p><strong>ACT</strong>:</p>

<ul>
	<li>251(2)(c)(i)</li>
	<li>Unrelated persons are dealing at arm's length is a question of fact: 251(1)(c)</li>
</ul></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><button class="btn btn-success popup-modal-dismiss" type="button">End</button></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-781218">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-102">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-103">Who are the persons?</a> – Corporations</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4778" id="wb-auto-104">Are the persons controlling each corporation related?</a> – Each corporation is related to the same third corporation                                                                                            </li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p><strong>RESULT</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-fw fa-times-circle" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:14px">&nbsp;</span>Where two corporations are related to the same third corporation, they are deemed to be related to each other.</p>

<div style="background:#eeeeee; border:1px solid #cccccc; margin-left:40px; padding:5px 10px">Person includes a partnership&nbsp;for the purpose of:<br>
&nbsp; &nbsp;-&nbsp;CEWS and CERS claims<br>
&nbsp; &nbsp;- GST/HST</div>

<p><br>
<strong>EXAMPLE</strong>:</p>

<ul>
	<li>Cecilia and Rita are sisters. Cecilia is the sole shareholder of Ceci&nbsp;Co. Rita is the sole shareholder of Rita Co.</li>
	<li>Cecilia has a daughter, Tatiana. Tatiana is the sole shareholder of Tatiana Co.</li>
	<li>Ceci Co is related to Rita Co (sisters). Ceci Co is also related to Tatiana Co (mother and daughter).&nbsp;</li>
</ul>

<p style="margin-left:40px">If not for this provision, Rita Co and Tatiana Co would not be related, since an aunt is not related to her neice. However, since Ceci Co is related to both Rita Co and Tatiana Co, Rita Co and Tatiana Co are deemed to be related to each other.</p>

<p><strong>ACT</strong>:</p>

<ul>
	<li>251(3)</li>
	<li>Not dealing at arm's length: 251(1)(a)</li>
</ul></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><button class="btn btn-success popup-modal-dismiss" type="button">End</button></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-4780">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-105">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-106">Who are the persons?</a> – A corporation and a person (or group of persons)</li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"><p>Is the corporation related to any persons?</p></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p>To find out if a person is related to a corporation, you must determine who controls the corporation.&nbsp;</p>

<p><span class="fa fa-exclamation-triangle fa-fw" style="font-size:14px">&nbsp;</span> For a single person to control a corporation, the person&nbsp;<strong>must have more than 50% (50% + 1)&nbsp;</strong>of the voting shares.</p>

<p><strong>EXAMPLE</strong>:&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">If 1,000,000 voting shares have been issued, a person would have to have 500,001 of the voting shares to control the corporation on their own.</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">The class of shares (and the rights attached to the shares) are described in the Articles of Incorporation. They can be changed only by amending the articles.</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">If only one class of shares has&nbsp;been issued, all shares in the corporation have the same rights. In this case, all shares would be voting shares.</p>

<p>For more information on shares and how they work, see&nbsp;<a href="https://www.ic.gc.ca/eic/site/cd-dgc.nsf/eng/cs06644.html" rel="external" target="_blank">Share structure and shareholders</a>.</p></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-936043" id="wb-auto-107">A person controls the corporation</a></li><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-844344" id="wb-auto-108">A related group of persons control the corporation</a></li><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-20459" id="wb-auto-109">A person is related to another person who controls the corporation</a></li><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-570157" id="wb-auto-110">The corporation is not controlled by one person or a related group of persons</a></li><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-408087" id="wb-auto-111">A person is related to a related group of persons who controls the corporation</a></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-936043">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-112">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-113">Who are the persons?</a> – A corporation and a person (or group of persons)</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4780" id="wb-auto-114">Is the corporation related to any persons?</a> – A person controls the corporation</li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p><strong>RESULT</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-fw fa-times-circle" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:14px">&nbsp;</span>A person that controls a corporation is related to the corporation. The person <strong>does not </strong>deal at arm's length with the corporation.</p>

<div style="background:#eeeeee; border:1px solid #cccccc; margin-left:40px; padding:5px 10px">Person includes a partnership&nbsp;for the purpose of:<br>
&nbsp; &nbsp;-&nbsp;CEWS and CERS claims<br>
&nbsp; &nbsp;- GST/HST</div>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>EXAMPLE</strong>:</p>

<ul style="margin-left:40px">
	<li>Amy owns 60% of the voting shares in AM&nbsp;Corp.</li>
	<li>Mike owns the remaining 40%.</li>
	<li>Since Amy owns more than 50% of the voting shares, Amy controls AM&nbsp;Corp.</li>
</ul>

<p style="margin-left:40px">Amy <strong>does not</strong> deal at arm's length with AM&nbsp;Corp. If Mike is not related to Amy or otherwise related to AM Corp by other means, Mike may deal at arm's length with AM Corp.</p>

<p><strong>ACT</strong>:</p>

<ul>
	<li>251(2)(b)(i)</li>
	<li>Not dealing at arm's length: 251(1)(a)</li>
</ul></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><button class="btn btn-success popup-modal-dismiss" type="button">End</button></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-844344">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-115">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-116">Who are the persons?</a> – A corporation and a person (or group of persons)</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4780" id="wb-auto-117">Is the corporation related to any persons?</a> – A related group of persons control the corporation</li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p><strong>RESULT</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-fw fa-times-circle" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:14px">&nbsp;</span>A related group that controls a corporation is related to the corporation. They <strong>do not </strong>deal at arm's length with the corporation.</p>

<div style="background:#eeeeee; border:1px solid #cccccc; margin-left:40px; padding:5px 10px">Person includes a partnership&nbsp;for the purpose of:<br>
&nbsp; &nbsp;-&nbsp;CEWS and CERS claims<br>
&nbsp; &nbsp;- GST/HST</div>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>EXAMPLE</strong>:</p>

<ul style="margin-left:40px">
	<li>Warren, Fred and Mike each own 1/3 of the voting shares of WFM Corp.</li>
	<li>Warren and Fred are common-law partners.</li>
	<li>Since Warren and Fred are related to each other and together they own&nbsp;66.7% (more than 50%) of the voting shares, they are a related group that controls WFM Corp.</li>
</ul>

<p style="margin-left:40px">Warren and Fred <strong>do not </strong>deal at arm's length with WFM Corp. If Mike is not related to either Warren or Fred&nbsp;or otherwise related to WFM Corp by other means, Mike may deal at arm's length with WFM Corp.</p>

<p><strong>ACT</strong>:</p>

<ul>
	<li>251(2)(b)(ii)</li>
	<li>Not dealing at arm's length: 251(1)(a)</li>
</ul></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><button class="btn btn-success popup-modal-dismiss" type="button">End</button></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-20459">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-118">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-119">Who are the persons?</a> – A corporation and a person (or group of persons)</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4780" id="wb-auto-120">Is the corporation related to any persons?</a> – A person is related to another person who controls the corporation</li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p><strong>RESULT</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-fw fa-times-circle" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:14px">&nbsp;</span>A person that controls a corporation is related to the corporation. Another person that is related to that person is related to the corporation. That&nbsp;person&nbsp;<strong>does not </strong>deal at arm's length with the corporation.</p>

<div style="background:#eeeeee; border:1px solid #cccccc; margin-left:40px; padding:5px 10px">Person includes a partnership&nbsp;for the purpose of:<br>
&nbsp; &nbsp;-&nbsp;CEWS and CERS claims<br>
&nbsp; &nbsp;- GST/HST</div>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>EXAMPLE</strong>:</p>

<ul style="margin-left:40px">
	<li>Amy owns 60% of the voting shares in AM&nbsp;Corp.</li>
	<li>Mike owns the remaining 40%.</li>
	<li>Since Amy owns more than 50% of the voting shares, Amy controls AM&nbsp;Corp.</li>
	<li>Amy is married to Alan.</li>
</ul>

<p style="margin-left:40px">As a result Alan is related to Amy and AM Corp. If Alan (or a related party) does business with AM Corp, he <strong>does not&nbsp;</strong>deal at arm's length with AM&nbsp;Corp.&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>ACT</strong>:</p>

<ul>
	<li>251(2)(b)(iii)</li>
	<li>Not dealing at arm's length: 251(1)(a)</li>
</ul></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><button class="btn btn-success popup-modal-dismiss" type="button">End</button></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-570157">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-121">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-122">Who are the persons?</a> – A corporation and a person (or group of persons)</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4780" id="wb-auto-123">Is the corporation related to any persons?</a> – The corporation is not controlled by one person or a related group of persons</li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p><strong>RESULT</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">The shareholders <strong>are not </strong>related to a corporation if more than 50% of the voting shares of the corporation are <strong>not</strong> owned by either:</p>

<ul style="margin-left:40px">
	<li>one person</li>
	<li>a related group of persons</li>
</ul>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-hand-o-right" style="color:#009900; font-size:18px">&nbsp;</span>To find out whether they deal at arm's length, go to <strong>Determine if unrelated persons deal at arm's length</strong>.</p>

<div style="background:#eeeeee; border:1px solid #cccccc; margin-left:40px; padding:5px 10px">Person includes a partnership&nbsp;for the purpose of:<br>
&nbsp; &nbsp;-&nbsp;CEWS and CERS claims<br>
&nbsp; &nbsp;- GST/HST</div>

<p style="margin-left:40px">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>EXAMPLE</strong>:</p>

<ul style="margin-left:40px">
	<li>Warren, Fred, Victor and Mike each own 25% of the voting shares of WFVM Corp.</li>
	<li>Warren and Fred are common-law partners.</li>
	<li>Warren and Fred are related and together own 50% of the voting shares.</li>
	<li>Since they do not own more than 50% of the voting shares, they<strong> are not</strong> a related group that controls WFVM Corp.</li>
	<li>Victor and Mike are not related to each other.</li>
</ul>

<p style="margin-left:40px">The shareholders <strong>are not</strong> related to WFVM.</p>

<p><strong>ACT</strong>:</p>

<ul>
	<li>251(2)(b)</li>
	<li>Unrelated persons are dealing at arm's length is a question of fact: 251(1)(c)</li>
</ul></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><button class="btn btn-success popup-modal-dismiss" type="button">End</button></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-408087">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-124">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-125">Who are the persons?</a> – A corporation and a person (or group of persons)</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4780" id="wb-auto-126">Is the corporation related to any persons?</a> – A person is related to a related group of persons who controls the corporation</li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p><strong>RESULT</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-fw fa-times-circle" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:14px">&nbsp;</span>A related group that controls a corporation is related to the corporation. Another person that is related to that related group of persons is related to the corporation. That&nbsp;person&nbsp;<strong>does not </strong>deal at arm's length with the corporation.</p>

<div style="background:#eeeeee; border:1px solid #cccccc; margin-left:40px; padding:5px 10px">Person includes a partnership&nbsp;for the purpose of:<br>
&nbsp; &nbsp;-&nbsp;CEWS and CERS claims<br>
&nbsp; &nbsp;- GST/HST</div>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>EXAMPLE</strong>:</p>

<ul>
	<li>Warren, Fred and Mike each own 1/3 of the voting shares of WFM Corp.</li>
	<li>Warren and Fred are common-law partners.</li>
	<li>Since Warren and Fred are related to each other and together they own&nbsp;more than 66.7% of the voting shares, they are a related group that controls WFM Corp.</li>
	<li>Fred's brother Neil is a supplier for WFM Corp.</li>
	<li>Neil is related to Warren and Fred and therefore to WFM Crop.</li>
</ul>

<p style="margin-left:40px">Neil <strong>does not </strong>deal at arm's length with WFM Corp.</p>

<p><strong>ACT</strong>:</p>

<ul>
	<li>251(2)(b)(iii)</li>
	<li>Not dealing at arm's length: 251(1)(a)</li>
</ul></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><button class="btn btn-success popup-modal-dismiss" type="button">End</button></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-4818">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-127">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-128">Who are the persons?</a> – Trusts                                              </li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"><p>What is the type of trust?</p></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p>Trusts are persons. Generally, the rules for determining if a trust is related to another person are the same as for other persons.</p>

<ul>
	<li>A <strong>bare trust </strong>exists where a trustee is merely vested with the legal title to property and has no other duty to perform or responsibilities to carry out as trustee, in relation to the property vested in the trust.</li>
	<li>A <strong>testamentary trust </strong>is a trust or estate that is generally created on and as result of the death of the person.&nbsp;</li>
	<li>A <strong>personal trust</strong><strong> </strong>(for 2016 and subsequent tax years) means:
	<ul>
		<li>a trust that arose on and as a consequence of the individual’s death if it meets the conditions to be&nbsp;a graduated rate estate</li>
		<li>a trust in which no beneficial interest was acquired for consideration payable to the trust or to any person or partnership that has made a contribution to the trust</li>
	</ul>
	</li>
	<li>An <strong>inter-vivos trust</strong> is any trust, other than a testamentary trust.&nbsp; <select><option value="0">List of inter-vivos trusts</option><option value="1">an amateur athlete trust</option><option value="2">an employee life and health trust</option><option value="3">an employee trust</option><option value="4">a prescribed master trust</option><option value="5">a trust governed by a deferred profit sharing plan</option><option value="6">an employee benefit plan</option><option value="7">an employees profit sharing plan</option><option value="8">a foreign retirement arrangement</option><option value="9">a pooled registered pension plan</option><option value="10">a registered disability savings plan</option><option value="11">a registered education savings plan</option><option value="12">a registered pension plan</option><option value="13">a registered retirement income fund</option><option value="15">a registered retirement savings plan</option><option value="16">a registered supplementary unemployment benefit plan</option><option value="17">a tax-free savings account</option><option value="18">a related segregated fund trust</option><option value="19">a retirement compensation arrangement trust</option><option value="20">a trust whose direct beneficiaries are one of the aforementioned trusts</option><option value="22">a health and welfare trust</option><option value="23">a trust governed by an eligible funeral arrangement</option><option value="25">a cemetery care trust</option><option value="27">a trust deemed in respect of a communal religious organization</option></select></li>
</ul></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-764438" id="wb-auto-129">Bare trust</a></li><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-4860" id="wb-auto-130">Personal trust</a></li><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-486739" id="wb-auto-131">Inter-vivos trusts and testamentary trusts that are not personal trusts</a></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-764438">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-132">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-133">Who are the persons?</a> – Trusts                                              </li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4818" id="wb-auto-134">What is the type of trust?</a> – Bare trust</li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p><strong>RESULT</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">A trust that is considered to be a bare trust&nbsp;acts&nbsp;as agent for the beneficiary.&nbsp;The CRA considers the beneficiary is the person dealing&nbsp;with other parties&nbsp;with respect to the trust property.</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-hand-o-right" style="color:#009900; font-size:18px">&nbsp;</span>To find out whether the beneficiary is related to those parties, go to <strong>A corporation and a person (or group of persons)</strong>.</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">The sole duty of a bare trustee is to convey legal title to the trust property on demand,&nbsp;on the instructions of the&nbsp;beneficial owner&nbsp;(beneficiary). The bare trustee does not have any independent power, discretion or responsibility pertaining to the trust property. The beneficiary&nbsp;retains the right to control and direct the trustee in all matters relating to the trust property.</p>

<p><strong>EXAMPLE</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">123 Property Trust holds property for A Corp (the beneficiary). The beneficiary&nbsp;directs the trustee in all matters relating to the property.&nbsp;The&nbsp;trustee does not have any independent power, discretion or responsibility pertaining to the&nbsp;property.</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">It is likely that 123 Property Trust is a bare trust. The benficiary&nbsp;instructs 123 Property Trust to transfer the property to B Corp. A Corp and B Corp are related to each other.&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">Because A Corp and B Corp are related to each other, the transfer of the property&nbsp;is a non-arms-length transaction.</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">Had the role of the trustee been different, for example, if the trustee had discretionary power or responsibility to manage the property, the trust&nbsp;would not be a bare trust. In that case, if 123 Property Trust was not related to B Corp, the transaction would be at arm's length.</p></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><button class="btn btn-success popup-modal-dismiss" type="button">End</button></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-4860">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-135">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-136">Who are the persons?</a> – Trusts                                              </li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4818" id="wb-auto-137">What is the type of trust?</a> – Personal trust</li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"><p>Is the personal trust a specified personal trust?</p></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p>A personal trust is a specified personal trust if it is <strong>not </strong>described in paragraphs 108(1)(a) to (e.1) <select><option value="0">List of inter-vivos trusts</option><option value="1">an amateur athlete trust</option><option value="2">an employee life and health trust</option><option value="3">an employee trust</option><option value="4">a prescribed master trust</option><option value="5">a trust governed by a deferred profit sharing plan</option><option value="6">an employee benefit plan</option><option value="7">an employees profit sharing plan</option><option value="8">a foreign retirement arrangement</option><option value="9">a pooled registered pension plan</option><option value="10">a registered disability savings plan</option><option value="11">a registered education savings plan</option><option value="12">a registered pension plan</option><option value="13">a registered retirement income fund</option><option value="15">a registered retirement savings plan</option><option value="16">a registered supplementary unemployment benefit plan</option><option value="17">a tax-free savings account</option><option value="18">a related segregated fund trust</option><option value="19">a retirement compensation arrangement trust</option><option value="20">a trust whose direct beneficiaries are one of the aforementioned trusts</option><option value="22">a health and welfare trust</option><option value="23">a trust governed by an eligible funeral arrangement</option><option value="25">a cemetery care trust</option><option value="27">a trust deemed in respect of a communal religious organization</option></select>.</p></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-674076" id="wb-auto-138">Yes</a></li><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-747293" id="wb-auto-139">No</a></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-674076">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-140">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-141">Who are the persons?</a> – Trusts                                              </li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4818" id="wb-auto-142">What is the type of trust?</a> – Personal trust</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4860" id="wb-auto-143">Is the personal trust a specified personal trust?</a> – Yes</li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p><strong>RESULT</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">A trust is a person.</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-hand-o-right" style="color:#009900; font-size:18px">&nbsp;</span>To find out if a trust is related to a corporation, see <strong>A corporation and a person (or group of persons)</strong>.&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-fw fa-times-circle" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:14px">&nbsp;</span>If the trust is related to a corporation, it does not deal at arm's length with the corporation.</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-fw fa-times-circle" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:14px">&nbsp;</span>A beneficiary <strong>does not</strong> deal&nbsp;at arm's length with the trust from which it acquired property in accordance with the terms of the will of the deceased.</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-fw fa-times-circle" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:14px">&nbsp;</span>Additionally,&nbsp;two or more specified personal trusts are deemed <strong>not </strong>to&nbsp;deal&nbsp;at arm's length in either of the following situations:</p>

<ul style="margin-left:40px">
	<li>the same person is a beneficiary of each trust</li>
	<li>a person who is a beneficiary of one trust does not deal at arm's length with a person who is a beneficiary of the other trust(s).</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>ACT</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">251(1)(b)</p></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><button class="btn btn-success popup-modal-dismiss" type="button">End</button></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-747293">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-144">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-145">Who are the persons?</a> – Trusts                                              </li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4818" id="wb-auto-146">What is the type of trust?</a> – Personal trust</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4860" id="wb-auto-147">Is the personal trust a specified personal trust?</a> – No</li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p><strong>RESULT</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">A trust is a person.</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-hand-o-right" style="color:#009900; font-size:18px">&nbsp;</span>To find out if a trust is related to a corporation, see <strong>A corporation and a person (or group of persons)</strong>.&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-fw fa-times-circle" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:14px">&nbsp;</span>If the trust is related to a corporation, it does not deal at arm's length with the corporation.</p></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><button class="btn btn-success popup-modal-dismiss" type="button">End</button></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-486739">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-148">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-149">Who are the persons?</a> – Trusts                                              </li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4818" id="wb-auto-150">What is the type of trust?</a> – Inter-vivos trusts and testamentary trusts that are not personal trusts</li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p><strong>RESULT</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">A trust is a person.</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-hand-o-right" style="color:#009900; font-size:18px">&nbsp;</span>To find out if a trust is related to a corporation, see <strong>A corporation and a person (or group of persons)</strong>.&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-fw fa-times-circle" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:14px">&nbsp;</span>If the trust is related to a corporation, it does not deal at arm's length with the corporation.</p></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><button class="btn btn-success popup-modal-dismiss" type="button">End</button></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-4781">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-151">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-152">Who are the persons?</a> – Partnerships                                                                                                                                                         </li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"><p>Is the partnership related to any persons?</p></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p>Under the Income Tax Act, partners are not normally related to a partnership and partnerships are not related to other persons. Control determines if&nbsp;partners or partnerships deal at arm's length with each other or another person.</p>

<p>A partner can control a partnership in two ways:</p>

<ul>
	<li>ownership of a controlling interest, by having more than a 50% share in the profits of the partnership</li>
	<li>a mandate vested in that partner by the other partners, by being granted decision making powers in the partnership agreement</li>
</ul>

<p><span class="fa fa-exclamation-triangle fa-fw" style="font-size:14px">&nbsp;</span> For GST/HST purposes, a partner is related to the partnership, regardless of control.</p></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-895613" id="wb-auto-153">A partner controls a partnership</a></li><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-614399" id="wb-auto-154">A partnership controls a corporation</a></li><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-423590" id="wb-auto-155">A related group of partners controls a partnership</a></li><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-844078" id="wb-auto-156">No partner or related group of partners controls the partnership</a></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-895613">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-157">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-158">Who are the persons?</a> – Partnerships                                                                                                                                                         </li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4781" id="wb-auto-159">Is the partnership related to any persons?</a> – A partner controls a partnership</li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p><strong>RESULT</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-fw fa-times-circle" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:14px">&nbsp;</span>The partner <strong>does not</strong> deal at arm's length with the partnership.</p>

<p><strong>EXAMPLE</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">Dylan, Leonard, Donovan and Sarah form a partnership. They are not related to each other and each has an equal 25% share in the profits.</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">Under the partnership agreement, Sarah manages the business and has full decision making authority. Since Sarah controls the partnership, she <strong>does not</strong> deal at arm's length with the partnership.&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">For income tax purposes,&nbsp;Dylan, Leonard and&nbsp;Donovan deal at arm's length with the partnership based on control, though they may <strong>not</strong> deal at arm's length based on other factors.&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">For GST/HST purposes, all partners are related to the partnership. They&nbsp;<strong>do not </strong>deal at arm's length with the partnership.</p>

<p><strong>ACT</strong>:</p>

<ul>
	<li>126(3) of the Excise Tax Act</li>
	<li>251(1)(c) of the Income Tax Act</li>
	<li>Not dealing at arm's length: 251(1)(a)</li>
</ul></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><button class="btn btn-success popup-modal-dismiss" type="button">End</button></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-614399">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-160">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-161">Who are the persons?</a> – Partnerships                                                                                                                                                         </li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4781" id="wb-auto-162">Is the partnership related to any persons?</a> – A partnership controls a corporation</li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p><strong>RESULT</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-fw fa-times-circle" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:14px">&nbsp;</span>The partnership <strong>does not</strong> deal at arm's length with a corporation.</p>

<p><strong>EXAMPLE</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">Dylan and&nbsp;Leonard&nbsp;form DyLo&nbsp;partnership. Dylan,&nbsp;Leonard&nbsp;and DyLo&nbsp;partnership&nbsp;are shareholders in a corporation, DL Corp. Dylan and&nbsp;Leonard are not related to each other.</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">The voting shares in DL Corp are distributed as follows:</p>

<ul style="margin-left:40px">
	<li>DyLo partnership - 60%</li>
	<li>Dylan - 20%</li>
	<li>Leonard - 20%</li>
</ul>

<p style="margin-left:40px">For income tax purposes:</p>

<ul style="margin-left:40px">
	<li>DyLo Partnership<strong> does not </strong>deal at arm's length with&nbsp;DL Corp.</li>
	<li>Based on control, Dylan and Leonard deal at arm's length with DL Corp, though they may not deal at arm's length based on other factors.</li>
</ul>

<p style="margin-left:40px">For GST/HST purposes:</p>

<ul style="margin-left:40px">
	<li>DyLo Partnership is related to DL Corp. DyLo Partnership&nbsp;<strong>does not </strong>deal at arm's length with DL Corp.</li>
	<li>Dylan and Leonard are:
	<ul>
		<li>related to DyLo Partnership</li>
		<li><strong>not</strong> part of a related group that controls the corporation</li>
		<li><strong>not</strong> related to DL Corp&nbsp;</li>
	</ul>
	</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>ACT</strong>:</p>

<ul>
	<li>126(3) of the Excise Tax Act</li>
	<li>251(1)(c) of the Income Tax Act</li>
	<li>Not dealing at arm's length: 251(1)(a)</li>
</ul></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><button class="btn btn-success popup-modal-dismiss" type="button">End</button></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-423590">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-163">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-164">Who are the persons?</a> – Partnerships                                                                                                                                                         </li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4781" id="wb-auto-165">Is the partnership related to any persons?</a> – A related group of partners controls a partnership</li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p><strong>RESULT</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-fw fa-times-circle" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:14px">&nbsp;</span>The related group of partners <strong>does not</strong> deal at arm's length with the partnership.</p>

<p><strong>EXAMPLE</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">Dylan, Leonard, Donovan and Sarah form a partnership. Leonard, Donovan and Sarah are siblings (related). Dylan is their cousin (<strong>not</strong> related). Each has an equal 25% share in the profits.</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">Since&nbsp;they are a related group that controls the partnership, Leonard, Donovan and Sarah <strong>do&nbsp;not</strong> deal at arm's length with the partnership.&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">For income tax purposes,&nbsp;Dylan deals at arm's length with the partnership based on control, though he may <strong>not</strong> deal at arm's length based on other factors.&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">For GST/HST purpsoes, all partners are related to the partnership. They&nbsp;<strong>do not </strong>deal at arm's length with the partnership.</p>

<p><strong>ACT</strong>:</p>

<ul>
	<li>126(3) of the Excise Tax Act</li>
	<li>251(1)(c) of the Income Tax Act</li>
	<li>Not dealing at arm's length: 251(1)(a)</li>
</ul></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><button class="btn btn-success popup-modal-dismiss" type="button">End</button></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-844078">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-166">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – No - Determine if persons are related</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4775" id="wb-auto-167">Who are the persons?</a> – Partnerships                                                                                                                                                         </li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4781" id="wb-auto-168">Is the partnership related to any persons?</a> – No partner or related group of partners controls the partnership</li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p><strong>RESULT</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">For income tax purposes, the partners are <strong>not</strong> related since they don't have more than 50% of the share of the profits. &nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-hand-o-right" style="color:#009900; font-size:18px">&nbsp;</span>To find out whether they deal at arm's length based on other factors, go to <strong>Determine if unrelated persons deal at arm's length</strong>.</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-fw fa-times-circle" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:14px">&nbsp;</span>For GST/HST purposes, the partners are related to the partnership.&nbsp;They&nbsp;<strong>do not </strong>deal at arm's length with the partnership.</p>

<p><strong>EXAMPLE</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">Dylan, Leonard, Donovan and Sarah form a partnership. The 4 individuals are not related to each other. Each has an equal 25% share in the profits and has an equal say in the decision making process for the partnership.</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">For income tax purposes,&nbsp;Dylan, Leonard,&nbsp;Donovan and Sarah deal at arm's length with the partnership based on control, though they may <strong>not</strong> deal at arm's length based on other factors.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">For GST/HST purposes, all partners are related to the partnership. They&nbsp;<strong>do not </strong>deal at arm's length with the partnership.</p>

<p><strong>ACT</strong>:</p>

<ul>
	<li>126(3) of the Excise Tax Act</li>
	<li>Unrelated persons are dealing at arm's length is a question of fact: 251(1)(c) of the Income Tax Act</li>
</ul></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><button class="btn btn-success popup-modal-dismiss" type="button">End</button></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-4874">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-169">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – Yes, the persons are not related - Determine if unrelated persons deal at arm's length</li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"><p>Determine&nbsp;if unrelated persons deal at arm's length. What is the relationship of the parties?</p></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p>Unrelated persons may or may not deal with each other at arm's length. The following criteria have generally been used by the courts to determine&nbsp;whether parties in a transaction are&nbsp;<strong>not&nbsp;</strong>dealing at arm's length:</p>

<ul>
	<li>whether there is a common mind which directs the bargaining for both parties to a transaction</li>
	<li>whether the parties to a transaction act in concert without separate interests</li>
	<li><em>de facto&nbsp;</em>control (refers to the ability to influence the decisions of others directly or indirectly)</li>
</ul>

<p>The courts have held that excessive or constant advantage, authority or influence can constitute <em>de facto</em> control. This advantage does not have to be exercised to be a factor. The mere ability to do so is sufficient.</p>

<p>The <strong>three tests combined</strong> will help determine if the influence by one party over the other would be sufficient&nbsp;that the other party is no longer free to participate in the transaction in an independent manner.</p>

<p><strong>ACT</strong>:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">251(1)(c)</p></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-229527" id="wb-auto-170">Supplier/buyer</a></li><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-245813" id="wb-auto-171">Employer/employee</a></li><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-247163" id="wb-auto-172">Landlord/tenant - CERS</a></li><li><a class="wb-lbx btn btn-default mrgn-bttm-md" href="#dt-78070" id="wb-auto-173">Shareholder/corporation</a></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-229527">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-174">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – Yes, the persons are not related - Determine if unrelated persons deal at arm's length</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4874" id="wb-auto-175">Determine&nbsp;if unrelated persons deal at arm's length. What is the relationship of the parties?</a> – Supplier/buyer</li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><h2>Result</h2>

<div style="background:#fff2cc; border:1px solid #cccccc; padding:5px 10px"><strong>Do not </strong>make&nbsp;an arm's length determination unless you have access to all the relevant facts and the ability to analyse those facts.&nbsp;</div>

<p><br>
The following combined factors may be an indicator that the buyer is <strong>not dealing at arm's length</strong> with an unrelated supplier.</p>

<h3><span class="fa fa-list" style="color:#808080; font-size:25px">&nbsp;</span>Connection</h3>

<p style="margin-left:40px">This connection could be a relationship or it could be based on needs. Their relationship may have the attributes of related persons without being related. For example:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>a significant, but non-controlling interest in a corporation</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>a distant relative (aunts, uncles, nieces, nephews, cousins)</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>former spouses, friends, acquaintances, former colleagues, former classmates</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>individual needs related to a business deal, a legal issue, a debt, etc connecting 2 or more persons&nbsp;</p>

<h3><span class="fa fa-list" style="color:#808080; font-size:25px">&nbsp;</span> Transaction - Fair market value</h3>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>A transaction carried on below or above fair market value may be an indication that parties are not dealing at arm's length.</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>The fact that two interconnected persons carry out a transaction for above or below fair market value, is not sufficient to conclude that these persons are not dealing with each other at arm's length. &nbsp;</p>

<h3><span class="fa fa-list" style="color:#808080; font-size:25px">&nbsp;</span>Analysis&nbsp;</h3>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>Is there a hidden benefit, unrelated to the transaction that one or both parties appear to be working towards?</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>Does it appear that one party is not acting for theior own&nbsp;benefit, but may be enabling the other party to realize a separate goal?&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>Does one party appear to make concessions with no apparent benefit for doing so?</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>Does one (or both) parties obtain a personal (non-business) benefit from completing the transaction?</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>Is the payment schedule different from similar arm's length transactions?</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>If payment is based on the completion of work, were the terms of the contract carried out?</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>If the transaction is a barter transaction, how were the properties valued? Was there a lien against any of the exchanged property?</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>Is there a contract between the parties? Does the contract define how the responsibilities, risks and benefits are divided between the parties? If not, are there other communications that outline the terms?</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>Does the conduct of the parties indicate that the terms of the contract were carried out?</p>

<h3><span class="fa fa-list" style="color:#808080; font-size:25px">&nbsp;</span>Combined factors</h3>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>A connection, along with a non-fair market value transaction combined with the answer to one or more of the questions in the analysis could be an indication that the parties <strong>do not </strong>deal at arm's length.</p>

<h3><span class="fa fa-cogs" style="font-size:25px">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>Example</h3>

<p style="margin-left:40px">Ownerco is a landlord. Renterco is an unrelated tenant. Although the two corporations are unrelated, there are indications that there are connections between the two. The lease between Ownerco and Renterco requires Renterco to pay $30 per square foot.&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">Other leases signed around the same time for similar properties of similar size in the same area have been signed for $40 per square foot.&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">The fact that a below market lease was signed is not sufficient to say the two parties acted under a common mind. However, if Ownerco received another benefit (perhaps access to another contract) as a result of their deal, this would be an indication that the parties did not act at arm's length.</p>

<h3><span class="fa fa-plus-square" style="font-size:30px">&nbsp;</span>More information</h3>

<p style="margin-left:40px">For a synopsis of court cases dealing with arm's length, see Tax Interpretations, <a href="https://taxinterpretations.com/tax-topics/income-tax-act/section-251#term-129611" rel="external" target="_blank">Subsection 251(1) - Arm's length</a>.</p></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><button class="btn btn-success popup-modal-dismiss" type="button">End</button></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-245813">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-176">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – Yes, the persons are not related - Determine if unrelated persons deal at arm's length</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4874" id="wb-auto-177">Determine&nbsp;if unrelated persons deal at arm's length. What is the relationship of the parties?</a> – Employer/employee</li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><h2>Result</h2>

<div style="background:#fff2cc; border:1px solid #cccccc; padding:5px 10px"><strong>Do not </strong>make an arm's length determination unless you have access to all the relevant facts and the ability to analyse those facts.&nbsp;</div>

<p><br>
The following combined factors may be an indicator that the employer is <strong>not dealing at arm's length</strong> with a related worker.</p>

<h3><span class="fa fa-list" style="color:#808080; font-size:25px">&nbsp;</span>Rate of pay/work hours</h3>

<h4 style="margin-left:40px"><strong>The rate of pay:</strong></h4>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>is inconsistent with the labour market (either excessive or inadequate)</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>does not reflect the worker's qualifications</p>

<h4 style="margin-left:40px"><strong>The worker:</strong></h4>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>is paid in a different manner than the other employees of the business</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>receives benefits that are not offered to an unrelated worker performing similar duties (for example, bonuses, vacation pay, paid vacation, overtime pay)</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>performs&nbsp;work that is important to the operation of the business with no pay</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>receives&nbsp;substantial wages or advances prior to work performed</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>is paid infrequently or irregularly when compared to unrelated workers&nbsp;</p>

<h3><span class="fa fa-list" style="color:#808080; font-size:25px">&nbsp;</span>Terms and conditions of employment</h3>

<h4 style="margin-left:40px"><strong>Compared to other workers, the worker:</strong></h4>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>has more freedom to “come and go” and conduct personal errands during work hours</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>has a more flexible work schedule&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>does not have their hours of work tracked or recorded</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>has the flexibility to work away from the work-site</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>has the ability to make significant decisions that don't match the position</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>is able to use business-owned assets without accounting for the use</p>

<h3><span class="fa fa-list" style="color:#808080; font-size:25px">&nbsp;</span>Nature and importance of work performed</h3>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>The worker does not have the credentials, knowledge or related work experience to perform the duties</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>There was not enough work in the employer's business to warrant the hiring of the worker to work full time</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>The duties performed by the worker are not an integral part of or are insignificant to the employer's business</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>The worker performs duties historically performed by the employer</p>

<h3><span class="fa fa-list" style="color:#808080; font-size:25px">&nbsp;</span>Combined factors</h3>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>A review of the above factors may be an indication that the parties <strong>do not </strong>deal at arm's length. The more factors that apply, the stronger the indication.</p>

<h3><span class="fa fa-plus-square" style="font-size:30px">&nbsp;</span>More information</h3>

<p style="margin-left:40px">For more information, see&nbsp;<a href="https://infozone.omega.dce-eir.net/english/r2110203/c/0500/518/13_016-e.asp" onclick="window.open(this.href, '', 'resizable=no,status=no,location=no,toolbar=no,menubar=no,fullscreen=no,scrollbars=no,dependent=no,width=1200,left=300,height=600,top=50'); return false;" rel="external">CPP/EI Appeals, indicators of possible non-arm's length relationships</a>.</p></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><button class="btn btn-success popup-modal-dismiss" type="button">End</button></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-247163">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-178">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – Yes, the persons are not related - Determine if unrelated persons deal at arm's length</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4874" id="wb-auto-179">Determine&nbsp;if unrelated persons deal at arm's length. What is the relationship of the parties?</a> – Landlord/tenant - CERS</li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><h2>Result</h2>

<div style="background:#fff2cc; border:1px solid #cccccc; padding:5px 10px"><strong>Do not </strong>make&nbsp;an arm's length determination unless you have access to all the relevant facts and the ability to analyse those facts.&nbsp;</div>

<p><br>
The following combined factors may be an indicator that the buyer is <strong>not dealing at arm's length</strong> with an unrelated supplier.</p>

<h3><span class="fa fa-list" style="color:#808080; font-size:25px">&nbsp;</span>Connection</h3>

<p style="margin-left:40px">This connection could be a relationship or it could be based on needs. Their relationship may have the attributes of related persons without being related. For example:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>a significant, but non-controlling interest in a corporation</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>a distant relative (aunts, uncles, nieces, nephews, cousins)</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>former spouses, friends, acquaintances, former colleagues, former classmates</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>individual needs related to a business deal, a legal issue, a debt, etc connecting 2 or more persons&nbsp;</p>

<h3><span class="fa fa-list" style="color:#808080; font-size:25px">&nbsp;</span> Transaction - Fair market value</h3>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>A lease entered into&nbsp;below or above fair market value may be an indication that parties are not dealing at arm's length.</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>The fact that two interconnected persons enter into an agreement for above or below fair market value, is not sufficient to conclude that these persons are not dealing with each other at arm's length. &nbsp;</p>

<h3><span class="fa fa-list" style="color:#808080; font-size:25px">&nbsp;</span>Analysis&nbsp;</h3>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>Has either party indicated association with the other on a Schedule 9 or Schedule 23?</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span> Do the landlord and tenant share the same contacts or have other common ties?</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px"></span>&nbsp; Is there a hidden benefit, unrelated to the lease agreement&nbsp;that one or both parties appear to be working towards?</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>Does it appear that one party is not acting for their own&nbsp;benefit, but may be enabling the other party to realize a separate goal?&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>Does one party appear to make concessions with no apparent benefit for doing so?</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>Does one (or both) parties obtain a personal (non-business) benefit from entering the agreement?</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>Is the payment schedule different from similar arm's length leases the landlord has with other tenants?</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>Does the lease&nbsp;define how the responsibilities, risks and benefits are divided between the parties? Does the conduct of the parties indicate that the terms of the lease are adhered to?</p>

<h3><span class="fa fa-list" style="color:#808080; font-size:25px">&nbsp;</span>Combined factors</h3>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>A connection, along with a non-fair market value lease agreement combined with the answer to one or more of the questions in the analysis could be an indication that the parties <strong>do not </strong>deal at arm's length.</p>

<h3><span class="fa fa-cogs" style="font-size:25px">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>Example 1 - arm's length</h3>

<h4 style="margin-left:40px"><strong>Landlord</strong></h4>

<ul style="margin-left:40px">
	<li>The landlord is Gold Mine Inc.</li>
	<li>The shares of Gold Mine Inc. are owned by Eric (33%), Floyd (33%) and Roger (33%). Eric, Floyd and Roger are not related to each other.</li>
</ul>

<h4 style="margin-left:40px"><strong>Tenant</strong></h4>

<ul style="margin-left:40px">
	<li>Lakeview Inc. is the tenant. It is wholly owned by Moonlight Inc.</li>
	<li>Luke is the director of Moonlight Inc. He also owns 50% of the shares.&nbsp;The remaining 50% are owned by North Star Financial LP</li>
	<li>The general partner of North Star Financial LP is Gold Mine Inc. Although they have a history with each other, none of the shareholders of Gold Mine Inc. are related to Luke.</li>
</ul>

<h4 style="margin-left:40px">&nbsp;<strong>Analysis</strong></h4>

<p style="margin-left:80px">The landlord and the tenant are not related to each other. Gold Mine Inc. and Moonlight Inc. have not indicated an association with each other using Schedule 23.</p>

<p style="margin-left:80px">The lease between Gold Mine Inc. and Lakeview Inc. is a standard market rate net lease. It is similar to leases Gold Mine Inc. has with other tenants. There is no indication that either side has failed to fulfil the terms of the lease.</p>

<p style="margin-left:80px">A review of the Moonlight Inc. and Lakeview Inc. corporate minute books indicate Luke makes all decisions and has full control of the tenant corporation. There is no indication of control over Moonlight Inc. by North Star Financial LP.<br>
&nbsp;<br>
It appears likely that the landlord and tenant deal with each other at arm's length. The tenant,&nbsp;Lakeview Inc. is eligible to apply for CERS for the rent it pays to Gold Mine Inc.</p>

<h3><span class="fa fa-cogs" style="font-size:25px">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>Example 2 - Non-arm's-length</h3>

<h4 style="margin-left:40px"><strong>Landlord</strong></h4>

<ul style="margin-left:40px">
	<li>
	<p>The landlord is Ownerco</p>
	</li>
	<li>The shares of Ownerco are owned by Marley (50%) and Bob (50%). Marley and Bob are not related to each other.</li>
</ul>

<h4 style="margin-left:40px"><strong>Tenant</strong></h4>

<ul style="margin-left:40px">
	<li>
	<p>The tenant is Renterco</p>
	</li>
	<li>Olivia owns 50% of the shares of Renterco.&nbsp;The remaining 50% are owned by Xanadu Inc</li>
	<li>Marley owns 100% of the shares of Xanadu Inc.</li>
</ul>

<h4 style="margin-left:40px"><strong>Analysis</strong></h4>

<p style="margin-left:80px">The landlord and the tenant are not related to each other.&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-left:80px">The lease between Ownerco&nbsp;and Renterco&nbsp;is a standard net lease, although it appears to be below market. A review of invoices and bank statements demonstrates that Renterco has made late rent payments with no late payment or interest charges.</p>

<p style="margin-left:80px">A review of the Ownerco and Renterco corporate minute books indicate Marley is involved in the decisions made by both corporations.&nbsp; Additionally,&nbsp;Ownerco indicated that it is associated with Xanadu Inc. on its Schedule 23.</p>

<p style="margin-left:80px">It appears likely that the landlord and tenant <strong>do not</strong> deal with each other at arm's length. Renterco is <strong>not </strong>eligible for CERS on rent paid to a non-arms-length <span style="background-color:#f1c40f">landlord</span>. The landlord,&nbsp;Ownerco may eligible to claim mortgage&nbsp;interest, property taxes and property insurance.</p>

<h3><span class="fa fa-plus-square" style="font-size:30px">&nbsp;</span>More information</h3>

<p style="margin-left:40px">For a synopsis of court cases dealing with arm's length, see Tax Interpretations, <a href="https://taxinterpretations.com/tax-topics/income-tax-act/section-251#term-129611" rel="external" target="_blank">Subsection 251(1) - Arm's length</a></p></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><button class="btn btn-success popup-modal-dismiss" type="button">End</button></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-78070">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-180">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – Yes, the persons are not related - Determine if unrelated persons deal at arm's length</li><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4874" id="wb-auto-181">Determine&nbsp;if unrelated persons deal at arm's length. What is the relationship of the parties?</a> – Shareholder/corporation</li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><h2>Result</h2>

<div style="background:#fff2cc; border:1px solid #cccccc; padding:5px 10px"><strong>Do not </strong>make&nbsp;an arm's length determination unless you have access to all the relevant facts and the ability to analyse those facts.&nbsp;</div>

<p><br>
The following combined factors may be an indicator that the corporation is <strong>not dealing at arm's length</strong> with an unrelated shareholder.</p>

<h3><span class="fa fa-list" style="color:#808080; font-size:25px">&nbsp;</span>Connection</h3>

<p style="margin-left:40px">This connection could be a relationship or it could be based on needs. Their relationship may have the attributes of related persons without being related. For example:</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>a significant, but non-controlling interest in a corporation</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>a distant relative (aunts, uncles, nieces, nephews, cousins)</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>former spouses, friends, acquaintances, former colleagues, former classmates</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>individual needs related to a business deal, a legal issue, a debt, etc connecting 2 or more persons&nbsp;</p>

<h3><span class="fa fa-list" style="color:#808080; font-size:25px">&nbsp;</span>Analysis</h3>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>the percentage of voting shares in relation to other shareholders</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>ownership of a large debt of a corporation which may become payable on demand</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>a substantial investment in retractable preferred shares</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>shareholder agreements that include&nbsp;the holding of a casting vote</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>commercial or contractual relationships of the corporation that suggest, for example,&nbsp;economic dependence on a single supplier or customer</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>possession of a unique expertise that is required to operate the business</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>the influence that a family member, who is a shareholder, creditor, supplier, etc., of a corporation, may have over another family member who is a shareholder of the corporation</p>

<h3><span class="fa fa-list" style="color:#808080; font-size:25px">&nbsp;</span>Combined factors</h3>

<p style="margin-left:40px"><span class="fa fa-window-close-o" style="color:#cc0000; font-size:20px">&nbsp;</span>A connection between the parties combined with the answers to one or more of the questions in the analysis could be an indication that the parties <strong>do not </strong>deal at arm's length.</p>

<h3><span class="fa fa-cogs" style="font-size:25px">&nbsp;</span>EXAMPLE</h3>

<p style="margin-left:40px">Nalco's voting shares are divided amongst seven unrelated shareholders. No&nbsp;shareholder has control of the corporation on their own. However, Mr. X owns 46% of the shares. The other six shareholders each own 9% of the voting shares. This means Mr. X can make decisions for Nalco with agreement from any one of the six other shareholders. Mr. X is well-respected in the corporation and is&nbsp;influential in the community. Bob (a shareholder with 9% of the voting shares), has lately voted frequently with Mr. X.</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">On its own, this is not sufficient to conclude that Mr. X and Bob are <strong>not</strong> dealing with each other at arm's length. However, if they vote together to confer a benefit upon Mr. X that does not benefit the rest of the shareholders and Bob receives a valuable gift from Mr. X, this would be a strong indication that they were acting in concert with each other.</p>

<h3><span class="fa fa-plus-square" style="font-size:30px">&nbsp;</span>More information</h3>

<ul>
	<li>For more information, see&nbsp;IT-64R4, <a href="https://www.canada.ca/en/revenue-agency/services/forms-publications/publications/it64r4-consolid/archived-corporations-association-control.html" rel="external" target="_blank">Corporations: Association and Control</a></li>
	<li>For a synopsis of court cases dealing with arm's length, see Tax Interpretations, <a href="https://taxinterpretations.com/tax-topics/income-tax-act/section-251#term-129611" rel="external" target="_blank">Subsection 251(1) - Arm's length</a></li>
</ul></p><hr>		<ul class="dt-options list-inline mrgn-tp-lg mrgn-bttm-md"><li><button class="btn btn-success popup-modal-dismiss" type="button">End</button></li></ul>	</div><div class="modal-footer hidden"></div><button title="Close overlay (escape key)" type="button" class="mfp-close"><span aria-hidden="true" class="mfp-close">×</span></button></section><section aria-modal="true" class="mfp-hide modal-dialog modal-content dt-overlay" style="width:50%;" id="dt-85455">	<div class="modal-body">		<ol class="breadcrumb small mrgn-rght-lg tree-list-breadcrumb"><li><a class="wb-lbx" href="#dt-4283" id="wb-auto-182">Have you determined whether the persons are related?</a> – Resources and references                                                                                        </li></ol>		<h2 class="h3 mrgn-tp-0 brdr-bttm modal-header" style="padding: 0 1em 0 0;"></h2>		<p class="dt-question"><p><strong>Infozone</strong>:</p>

